This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of echo state networks (ESN), which are a type of recurrent neural network (RNN) and can be categorized under "Machine Learning" (cs.LG), "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI), and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper explores the behavior of randomized networks, which can be considered a topic in "Systems and Control" (cs.SD).
